<h2 id="the-decision">The Decision: 150 Basis Points</h2>

<p>On March 18, 2026, the Bank of Ghana's Monetary Policy Committee reduced the policy rate by 150 basis points to 14.0%. This continues an easing cycle that began from a peak of 29% in 2023, the emergency rate set during Ghana's debt crisis.</p>

<div class="data-box">
  <h4>The Numbers Behind the Decision</h4>
